caption: We had our first soft serve ice cream cones of the season here today. Belgian chocolate!!!!
Might be the best hamburger I’ve eaten.
Yummy veggie options, terrific fries, and delicious milkshakes!
Great Cheeseburger and fries!
My go to burger spot in the city
Their takeout is really great and the food is delicious.
Burger was amazing, but the garlic fries were disgusting, they literally just put spoonfuls of minced garlic on top of fries.

**PUBLIC SERVICE ANNOUNCEMENT** The “Mott Dog” is no longer the Mott Dog we all love and grew up with. It has changed to some seafood hot dog fusion (a very confused hot dog). It taste as bad as it sounds. Never again.

Burger definitely lived up to the hype. I could definitely taste the high quality meat and the burger travelled well. The French fries however were disappointing. I wasn’t expecting crinkle cut fries as it wasn’t what the images showed. Onions rings too lacked seasoning.

If you like soggy, over sauced food this is the place for you. I've had Asian Fusion before and this is not it. Would be good drunk food except they close at 12 on weekends.  Seems like they're going for the Starbucks ambiance by letting people post up and work all day at tables. For what it's worth, never have I been sush'ed (told to be quiet) at a restaurant, until I went to Mini Mott.
This burger hits different
Went to meet a client. Address is same as Mott. Well two things. Client lives above heavens kitchen.  2nd. I feel like I just took a plate of food from a heaven. wow. Wow. Amazing all the way.
Great burger and better fries! I don't know what kind of wizardry happens to make their truffle fry sauce but it's absolutely incredible, I would buy it by the gallon it I could hahaha

Hands down one of my favorite places in the city! I’ve never been disappointed by the food, the staff is friendly and helpful, outdoor dining is available n cute. I wish they had some kinda loyalty program or something but I’ll keep coming back regardless :)
I wish I knew about this place earlier instead of discovering it 2 weeks before I move out of state. Great food! The truffled fries were sooo good.
I got a beef sandwich here. It had a sauce like I've never had on a beef before, was like an Asian inspired mustard. My friends got burgers and said they were "Good for what it is."
Very good and esmall place to eat hamburguers and hoot dods
Shrimp po boy with garlic fries and a milkshake yummy!

Sooooo good. We have eaten in and ordered out and the quality was the same. The burgers at first seem like they will be too much, especially if you like your standard “good” burger but one bite and you will be sold. The ingredients and flavors are so well-balanced. It is absolutely delicious. And the fries reminded us of those amazing crispy cafeteria fries- I could not stop eating them. I want to try more thing on the menu but if I only ever got the Mott burger, I would be happy.

I really had a fantastic experience! Me & a friend met up here for lunch on a Wednesday afternoon. We decided to split the mini burger, made Da Bears style, an order of garlic confit fries, and an order of the Everything wings.  The mini mott made Da Bears style was perfect! It has black truffle, giardinera, fried onions, and gruyere cheese.... the patty itself was thin, but tasted great. If you want more meat you can order the double patty mott burger. I loved the way the gruyere just melted and blended everything together, and I would definitely order again.  The garlic confit fries were fantastic. The fries are cut thinner (think McDonald's size) and are covered in mouth watering, super flavorful garlic..... how can you really go wrong with this???  The Everything wings were fried to perfection. The sauce was like a sweet soy, and then they are sprinkled with Everything but the Bagel type seasoning. I really enjoyed this, but the wings themselves were kinda small. We were given an extra wing though, so I can't really complain. These were SO good I had to try the Hangry wings!  Hangry wings were my favorite! It's their take on buffalo, but with a subtle, but flavorful twist. I don't know if it was the sambal butter or what, but if they could bottle that sauce & sell it, I'd be very thankful.  They have beers & ciders too! I was way too full to try a soft serve, but I'll definitely be back. ONLY negative I could give this place is parking was hard to find, even at noon on a Wednesday.
Amazing banh mi and a great jackfruit burger too!
Eh.
I've been delivering to this restaurant for over a year and today I finally got some food, got the double burger and fries and was absolutely amazing. The side sauce was amazing!
One of my favorite burgers in the city! It's so unique and tasty.
Outstanding food and service
This place took number 1 burger spot in Chicago for me. Too good. Glad they opened up

Exquisite burgers that satisfy your cravings for a classic burger with an Asian twist. The garlic fries are great, but would not recommend eating them during a lunch break from work. The simplicity of Mini Mott’s menu makes things easy for the indecisive eaters while promising quality food each visit. Highly recommend checking out any of their food!
The Katsu Sandwich us delicious. The chicken is nice a crispy and the jam also is delicious. The wings are also delicious. Always delivered well and now one of my favorite places to order from.

Ordered for pickup and everything was amazing. We had the burger, shrimp po boy, both types of chicken wings and garlic fries. If everything was this great for delivery can’t imagine once we can have dine in!
A little pricey. But really good.
Great burgers! Some of the best in the city, no lie.

So I heard about Mini Mott through word of mouth. Which is something that every restaurant wants. It's for an interesting lay out. For the most part it's a bit crowded for my taste. There are 2 area in the front and in the back that are for big groups everyone is crammed into the middle section. The food itself is a bit over priced for my taste. I tried the original burger with bacon and cheese. (Safe bet) this was $8.95 plus a separate charge for the cheese and the bacon respectively. The fries I got were the garlic fries. One of the best parts of the experience though ago over priced. It was 3 dollars for a small basket. The amount of fries would be on par with like a kids fry from McDonald's. Towards the end of the experience I tried the chocolate ice cream taiyaki. This was the best part of the experience by far. The only thing I was not a fan of was the whole red beans at the bottom of the taiyaki. The flavor and texture didn't go well with the soft serve which was very very good. Overall I'd say the place was a bit over hyped and over priced, I wouldn't go out of my way to eat it again.
Great food and customer service
Finally got to try mini Mott and already planning my next visit! Outstanding, delicious, oh so amazing burgers! ❤️🍔
Hands down the best burger in Logan Square, if not Chicago
Naughty but nice! Chirpy guy at the counter gave us advice on the best things to order and everything was pretty great. Decor is fun, beer list is on point, music is vibes. A good all-rounder.

The original (double) burger was cooked perfectly and sandwiched in a fresh brioche bun. The list of toppings looked long, random, and heavy on fats -- sometimes a warning that a confused, underwhelming sandwich awaits you -- but they all melted together deliciously here. The miso butter sauce and crispy sweet potato strings were an especially tasty improvement on your average burger.  The side of fries is a taste portion of thin, short cut potatoes. Try them with fried garlic on top.
Excellent burgers, creative

The burger was good, but the fries and everything else were just ok. It's a casual place with counter service, and you can get in really easily as people are cycling through pretty quickly. Our pager didn't go off, so when they tracked us down the food was a little cold.
Buzzer never went off and park situation was a bit nutty. However, the burger was amazing and fries were fantastic. Staff were really nice too. Have high chairs for kids.

I saw a vlog on YouTube on Chicago and this place was suggested by a Chicago expert, also a tattoo artist. The place is around 15 mins away downtown in what I think is the north of the city. A very clean and beautiful neighborhood. I ordered their speciality beef burger and the fries. The drinks were nice too. I paid around $50 for 2 people. If you have time try other restaurants around mini Mott. Just look at the reviews and go for it!

I love this place,the food was so amazingly delicious.The mouth melting beef burger is out of the world. Even the overloaded Fries is something blast of flavours in your mouth. Only drawback is it's 12 mins drive from Chicago downtown.  Also if you want to try dumplings nearby try Fat Rice too.
Some of the best burgers I've eaten in a long time
Best burgers in Chicago, and one of the best in USA

I was super excited to try this place after reading the reviews but it was rather disappointing. The staff wasn’t pleasant and the restaurant was dirty (our water cups included). The food was okay but the whole experience had me wishing I had spent $50 anywhere else.  I really wanted to love this place because of the proximity to my work and home but I don’t think I will be going back :(
This place has one of the best burger I've ever had in my life! Get you one!
Really tasty and unique burgers and 🍟.

This place is a must! I had the chili cheese burger and hubs had the Truffle Shuffle. Both were outstanding! These burgers are messy and DELICIOUS!! The atmosphere is unique and cozy. It’s counter service which we don’t mind at all. Parking is challenging also. We loved it though. We will def be back!
Got the Original and an order of wings. Burger was great, wings were average. Managed expectations are key to enjoying this place.

The burgers here are honestly just okay. Not bad, but certainly nothing to be excited about. The meat and buns are unremarkable, and unique toppings can't save a burger that's average to begin with. For $10 each they're on the small side, and they can't keep up with a number of places around the area that don't even specialize in burgers. Atmosphere and service are great here though.

Excellent fusion burger. Fast service. Popped in for an order to go and was on my way in about 10 minutes. Recommend the burger and special fries, though their specials look on point as well. It's nice to have this place right off the square. I didn't indulge, but the beer list looks very good and the sweets are something I'll splurge on next time I stop in here. If dining in, the space is casual and comfortable.
If your looking for a non traditional burger, this is the place. Fun and funky vibe here. They have chicken wings that are fantastic. Garlic confit fries are a must. Try it out!
Interesting burgers and killer fries.
pretty small portions for the price.  It was tasty, but i wouldn't rush back.
Great burger.

Food was okay, nothing we'd crave to come back to though. I liked the jackfruit carnitas sandwich, but have had better. Apple pie shake was really good though! Prices were a little high, I'd be much happier with it if the burgers and sandwiches were about $2 cheaper. If it was cheaper we may return. Overall, it was okay but I'd likely only return for ice cream or a $3 beer during happy hour.
Super tasty burgers. The french fries are also extraordinary and the green peppers in sojasauce are to die for!
Rather exceptional tasting burgers and sandwiches. Belgian chocolate shake, however, is in a class by itself.
Pistachio cream ale was delicious. Wings were delicious. Sandwiches were good, but not blow my mind.
Quick service, excellent food, cool vibes.  Will be going back.
Fish cones baby
Very good burger. Interesting decor. The prices were a bit too high but this did not stop me from enjoying myself.

I have had Mini Mott on my radar for the past year. I finally went last night and my life has been changed!  I split the Original Burger, Hangry Wings, and Naked Fries with my boyfriend. Amazing!  The burger was juicy and fully loaded with multiple delicious condiments. I loved how saucy it was. The wings were perfection. The pickled jalapeños took them to a different level while the tzatziki dipping sauce helped control the heat.  We will definitely be coming back because I can't stop thinking about how good it was! Next time, I will be trying Da Bears Burger!
Amazing Japanese inspired burgers and hot dogs here!
Such a cute place with such nice ppl working there.  Love the music, and the garlic fries 😍

This place is such a wonderful neighborhood nook and a welcome next door neighbor to the New Wave. This block was always had an eerie feel in the PM and now it's bubbling and delightful. Their food choices are a bit limited and the servings as the title suggests, miniature (ish) but it's all made using high quality produce and gets prepped on the spot by the kindest crew of people. And the playlist is right on the money. What else?! The designer of this space truly know how to maximize on a rectangular and rather narrow spaces because they absolutely owned the space and made it feel at once inclusive yet intimate enough for an informal date. Also, bonus points for keeping spotless bathrooms. That's dope
Mott burger on lettuce wrap

Not a huge fan of this place, I think their burgers have too much sauce, they get soggy very quickly and do not travel at all. The only things worth getting are the wings, which are very good, and their ice cream.
Good outside sitting on a nice sunny day it would be Perfect table
Korean hamburger is delish.
Everything is tasty. That katsu sando* chicken sandwich is my fave.
Great food got the veggie burger. The jackfruit was made perfectly. Will definitely be back to grab a relaxing lunch again.
Great burger at a good price
Can’t go wrong with a burger and fries from this place. It’s a great spot to hang out with friends or get something to go.

Garlic fries are to die for!!! My mom and i shared thoes while she got a cobb salad and i got the katsu sando... salad was very pretty and perfectly dressed and my sandwhich was delightful! We will definatly be coming back!
I am not a good enough writer to convey how good this burger is.
Delicious burger! Loved the crispy sweet potato on the burger. Would highly recommend stopping by.

We went on a Sunday and the farmer's market is right in front.  Pretty cool.  Ordered: Mott Burger with egg Mini Burger Garlic fries Sweet corn shake (seasonal)  short walk from Logan Square train stop was really skeptical about the corn shake but...  Favorites: Mott Burger with egg (perfect balance, great bun...very very good) Sweet corn shake (so refreshing, usually not how i describe a shake...but it was really refreshing on a hot day)
Very good spot for different kinds of Chicago fare
Love their Burger!

The burger is interesting and garlic fries were good. They put too much on the burger, making it hard to taste the actual beef. Their aprons were so filthy I almost lost my appetite. Totally unacceptable and won't be back for this reason.
Great friendly service nice indoors and outdoors food looked delish Blueberry shake outstanding can make it boozy too
Love their katsu sandwich! The taiyaki ice cream is pretty gimmicky though.
Excellent burger. Definitely in my Chicago top 10. The sweet potato frizzles add a welcome crunch.
Damn that burger was good! Can't wait to come back and try the wings, shakes, and beers! Thank you
Good burger, great ice cream, and a good spot in Logan Square.
Best burger ever! Remember to add an egg on top!

I got a bacon burger and fries, and these fries were amazing. There was a ton of flavor in the burger, the bottom bun was a little soggy from all the delicious sauce and meat juices. But over all really delicious.
Its worth a meal there if you're in the area. I wasn't completely blown away with it but I did enjoy it. It's also a bit overpriced.
Great food and Friendly service!
Favorite spot for a quick bite or a low-key patio dinner. Friendly staff, quick service, killer food.
The food sucks! The drinks suck! The whole place actually!

It's not a bad burger though they have a heavy hand with sauce and sugar for just about everything,  even the shishito peppers and shrimp are on the sweet side. The soft serve ice cream is very good and oddly not overly sweet. The strawberry rhubarb seasonal flavor is exceptional. The burger is worth trying but hard to imagine being in regular rotation.
Great find in Logan Sq. Great food and beer selections.
This place doesn't disappoint, service and food are top notch! My favorite thing was the Katsu Sando but you can't go wrong with the Mott Burger.
Yummy burgers with great toppings
Had a milkshake with cheesy beef.Food was excellent.The had a really good hamburger for my 20 month old grandson made just for kids.
One of my favorite burgers in Chicago!
Best staff ever
Food was very delicious! Loved the Mott burger, and everything wings! The K pork skewer, katsu sando and garlic fries were all okay but wish portion sizes were bigger...Service was quick!
Very good but can get expensive quick. They recommend the garlic fries but they weren’t outstanding. Regulars are prob just as good. Wings were really good but the star of the show is the burger.
Great food
Best burger. Period.
Best burger in Chicago
Food was good, staff was polite.
Perfect spot for a casual, quick and delicious bite. Love the design, menu and beer selection. The Katsu sando transported me back to Japan.
We just went here for the taiyaki. It wasnt as Instagramable as some others looked but it sure was delicious. The seasonal flavor was vanilla chai and it was rich and cinnamon-y.

I wish I could give it 4.5 stars but I had to settle on 4. The burger was really good, nice and juicy and I like the shoestring potatoes on top. We also got a side skewer which was good and garlic fries which were not very good. Service was a little bit on the slow end even though they werent that busy. A solid burger, though.

Burgers on par with the Cheval’s interesting spices and topping packed. The ingredients were all fresh and led to a pleasant after-consumption heat.  We also got the Hangry wings which added a lighter than usual spin on the typical buffalo wings.  We were steered here from a local after Longman and Eagles’s kitchen was closed. Great recommendation Dave!
Dude, I was just there.
Fantastic unique burger 👌
Good smoothie
Jackfruit carnitas burger is heaven!
Great burgers ..
The best burger I have had in a long time. I loved the food and would definitely go back!
My favorite burger in Chicago!! The shishito peppers are awesome. Cute and cozy!

Casual 90's-esque burger spot with Asian influences. Great burger, fries, and fried shrimp. Could use some work on the salad. Chocolate ice cream was fantastic. The staff was incredibly friendly and informative. I'll definitely be back soon!!
Unique flavors. Decent price. Tastes like fresh ingredients.
10/10 would recommend! We got the mini burgers and hangry wings. It was all delicious 👍
Very very tasty burger!

caption: This place is small and easy to miss but was so worth it. Wish I could bring their split plea soup back to Texas with me!!
I like this place. It's very casual. Counter service. Creative burgers and wings. Beer. Could definitely bring the kids. It's cozy and inviting and I'll definitely be back.
I thought the burgers were delicious. The Chicago Bears specialty one was a must order!
Awesome burgers and shakes!
Great little spot.  Very small menu but it seems like they do everything right which is what matters more.

The burger is delicious and their garlic fries are amazing. Unfortunatly, it's not the most clean environment. The tables smell like they got cleaned by the same wet rag. And the last two times we went, we had a fly hovering over us.
Burger is no joke. Mini is key word here, in spacial terms.
Great food and ambience! Highly recommend this spot for lunch! Every bite we tried was better than the last!
Burgers are good, Ice cream is not worth the calories

After having the original burger at Mott Street it was time to see if Mini Mott stacked up...and it did. When you look at what goes on the burger it shouldn't work on paper but it does and it's amazing. Just make sure you get extra napkins, it's messy.

Had good food, pretty competitive by Logan standards. Cute interior, was well organized and presented in a welcoming manner with a good seating arrangement. Had a small bar, fit the motif of the place very well. Overall friendly service, good food, very cute location.

We came for dessert and unfortunately I was a bit underwhelmed. Tried the taiyaki and the cake portion was a bit stale and too tough. The ice cream flavorful, however maybe too much so. Also had a Belgian chocolate shake and it was a bit watered down, to the point of where it reminded me of a slightly melted Wendy's Frosty cone. Despite this the service was very good and friendly but is overshadowed by the lackluster dessert. I did not try their food, which did look enticing.
Good place for a burger and a beer.

Phenomenal burger. Best burger that I've had in Chicago (better than Owen and Engine, wayyyy better than Au Cheval).  The miso butter on the burger is what makes it so outstanding.  The sweet potato frizzles are also a nice touch.  Best to pair the burger with the Garlic Confit French fries and a cold beer.  We will be coming back over and over again when craving a burger.  Great job!

A place that holds its own! Nothing but, praise for their burger and fries! The perfect amount of juicy with a balanced mix of flavors and a great mouth feel. The fries are even better! A thin cut with crispness and flavor whether plain or their garlic. Check it out!
The Mott burger is delicious. The interior is a bit dated and the soft drinks are expensive ($3 can of soda). The outdoor seating area is very charming.
Very friendly staff! Single patty was just right with the garlic confit.
High quality burger patties with the right amount of sauce!  The place has a nice ambience.  On the pricey side though.
It's a little pricey, but a a fun spot. I haven't been to the full sized Mott, but I like the pared down menu of only a few items. Try the Taiyaki ice cream fish before summer ends!
Burgers are great but the shakes and ice cream are why you come back.
Kind of pricey but definitely worth the money the food was very delicious in flavor bowl I love the chicken wings there
Interesting retro/asian inspired atmosphere and menu. Classic Mott burger and garlic fries were amazing. Highly recommend you stop in and eat.

Cool atmosphere and environment and great burgers to go along with it. Really enjoyed the cripsy potato fries that were on top of the burger as well. Would recommend for a quick burger with substance and style!
Great food. Burgers, fries and wings. Good burgers. Garlic fries were perfect. The wings were terrific.
Fantastic burger- love the added spice. Expected garlic fries to be a little more tossed and coated instead of just a dollop of roasted garlic on the side.
I mean, it’s fine.

Very overpriced and the burgers are not  very good. I paid $53 for lunch for two, and there isn't even table service.  Order at the counter, pick up at the counter and bus your own table. No thanks! Not going back. Cannot recommend.

Mini Mott is great! They’re staff are very friendly and helpful, and there’s a lot of seating both inside and outside. Quick service too. I got the Mott burger and fries with their take on a vanilla shake. The food was delicious and so was the shake. The ONLY thing I would say is that the shake was pretty watery - it had the consistency of milk almost. So even though it tasted good, I didn’t drink very much of it.
SWEET CORN ICE CREAM  It was everything you’d imagine it to be, but better.  Also, wings were exceptional, but you already knew that.  Go naked with the fries.
Great burger with a sweet and savory aoli

This is a review for the food! not the service! everyone has been nice and attentive & helpful!  I want to love mini mott as much as I love mott st, but the food comparatively is hit or miss.  I’ve gone back a few times since its opening in early July. Mini Mott is very pricey for what you get. The burger is great, love the texture and crunch of the toppings. The confit fries were so soggy, and unsalted. The regular fries weren’t as well. So I pass on those whenever I go in. The wings are over cooked and dry every time. The sauce barley sticks to the wings, especially the everything wings. Which is such a shame, the everything wings at Mott st were so juicey, the skin is crisp and the sauce perfectly clings to the wings.  the one thing i can’t rectify is the soft serve. It is grainy, and seems as though there’s no fat content so it doesn’t have a smooth mouth feel. Ive tried a few flavors now, and each flavor is just a hint if what you’re expecting. I hope they work on this recipe as they go on.
Amazing burger, friendly staff, solid local drink selection
The burgers were good, but it's expensive and I can't necessarily say it was worth it. The original Mott st is fantastic though, and I would always recommend that.
Great burger with fast service
Nothing was that good and it was $20 for fast food for one person

I walk into the white brick building, entering the airy summery beach aesthetic. I see a burger pass by me, looks tasty. Then an appetizer of tteokbokki (yes I googled the spelling) throws me off, am I in the right place? I'm comforted by the sight of fries, all garlicky and gross in the best way. I look upon the drink menu, craft beers as expected and...what's that? $7 kombucha draft? Where am I? Oh yeah, Logan Square. Jokes aside this place is great. Affordable, nice outdoor seating, burgers, fries, ice cream, shakes. I'm sure it'll be a neighborhood staple.
Meh
Loved the burger
Burger, fries and wings were great. Ice cream was overrated.
One of the best burgers in Chicago.

Wow amazing burgers. I really need to get back there to try out the wings. I heard the wings are super good. Its a pretty interesting system they have where you show up no reservations, you can have a party of 40 and still you can't reserve. Just show up, pay at the counter and they give you a flashing little plastic disk which will buzz and flash when your food is ready. They give you small stainless steel cups to drink water from. And if you're there by yourself you can sit alone like a sad little man and eat your burger while starting at your phone. It's a really good place and I would love to go back but this time with other people. A lot of people, maybe 40. No reservations, first come first serve and they have a ton of alcoholic beverages for you to drink. Please drink responsibility.  Quite an enjoyable venue on a quicky developing stretch of Logan Blvd. There's a number of delicious restaurants all over this area and this is certainly a welcome addition to the fray.

The Mini Mott burger is a top five all time burger for me. It’s just perfect. I won’t try to describe it (besides that it’s messy), you should just go. Everything wings are good too, but I wish they had ranch. The fries were forgettable, the burger is really the star. Hip, buzzy space with Japanese trinket vending machines in the back.

This is a dope burger joint in the old Jam space. Unique tasting burgers with frizzy sweet potato and hoisin aioli. Good beer selection. Don’t miss out on the soft serve in the fish shaped cake cone... sick. Outdoor seating too. Pretty much on the square.

The burgers are flavorful but in small portions. The Mott burger are delicious, the fries are crispy, the chocolate milk shake ok (not creamy or thick enough), the cider good, and the seasonal burger good. Credit accepted, self serving and seating, the floor is VERY VERY slipper especially going to the restroom. Street parking available both metered and free.
Fun and hip place to eat a burger!  I loved the "Veg", the jackfruit burger.  It was delicious!
One of the best burgers I’ve had. The wings weren’t good. Service was okay. Will definitely come out to get a burger.

The service was outstanding (above and beyond for counter service), as expected from this team. The burger was fantastic! The fries were unforgivable. They didn’t stand up the garlic dressing (soggy) and the portion size was so small. So small. They’re potatoes. Charge me a dollar more if you must! But that portion is like Happy Meal size and should be doubled to be considered a side. I love you, Mott team! I wanted to come in for a burger tonight. But I walked over to Longman instead.  Also, the front is a bit of a cluster f* with the line, people picking up their food and that giant table.
What a great idea.  Fantastic burger and awesome wings.  Please don't go here to try it...I don't want to stand in line....

Went during the soft open and there was some confusion about seating but it was quickly sorted out. The space itself is cute and well decorated but tiny. Tables were very close together leaving little room to walk around which was problematic when it came to getting food from the counter. Food was very good. Burgers were delicious with the right amount of grease running down your arm. Fries were good but the garlic was on the bottom fries only which was disappointing. But the fries were perfectly cooked with the right amount of crunch. There are definitely more menu items I want to try like the wings and shakes so I'll definitely be going back soon!

Burger is AMAZING, especially with the egg. The garlic and naked fries were so good, also. The shakes were SOOOOO disappointing, although the flavor was good, it was just cold, frothy milk- not worth $5. I saw someone walk away with a soft serve in a cone that looked really good, so maybe skip the shake and get soft serve afterwards instead. Overall TOTALLY worth eating here, it was really satisfying.

We came here for the first night of their "soft opening" on a Thursday night.  Stood in line with others bec  The menu is very limited, but we did try some of the most popular items.  We both ordered the double Angus patty burgers (supposed to be 100% angus meat, american cheese, hoisin aioli, sweet potato frizzles, pickled jalapenos, pickles, miso butter and onions), the sauce is everything on this one, but the burger was very small, too thin and tasteless.  My burger was cooked, that's about all I can say about it that's any good.  It did not taste anything like Angus meat.  At $9.95, it is way overpriced.  We shared an order of the garlic confit fries (tossed in olive oil poached garlic) which were greasy and too soft for my taste.  I also ordered the Taiyaki (a large fish shaped waffle cone) with a combination of french vanilla and belgian chocolate soft serve ice cream.  I did not like this at all, the cone really tasted like a breakfast waffle, and the ice cream was nothing special.  They have a much larger selection of draft beers, priced from $5 to $7.  I tried the Kombucha on draft (Arize-dry hopped), which is a non-alchoholic drink that was supposed to be sweet, but was not and I did not like at all.  I will not be returning here as there are a lot better options in the neighborhood.
A very lively counter service restaurant with a great burger. The fries and ice cream cone are just okay, but the taiyaki is a really different and delicious dessert offering.

Love love this place. The burger is amazing as always, the garlic fries are to die for, and the chocolate shake was incredibly refreshing (not heavy at all!). Management and service were wonderful as well. You must go!!

Amazing burgers, but I was really surprised by the wings! The Everything wings come lathered in an amazing chili soy sauce that was so good we wanted to order a vat of it to take home. The burgers were also delicious, an elevated version of a classic burger, with sweet potato "frizzles" and pickled jalapeños. The garlic fries were also great, super well cooked with try perfect amount of crunch. The patio seating is a bit tight but still comfortable, and really enjoyable on a warm summer evening. I'll be interested to see what the space turns into in the wintertime. Overall, a great addition to the growing number of delicious options in Logan!

Mott St's incredible burger, now available in Logan Square at this fast, casual, and downright delicious new restaurant! Come for the burgers, stay for the Taiyaki cones. And the wings. And garlic fries. And cute Japanese vending machines in the back.
